title: Central European Pine Forest
description: A complete environment replicating a Central European Pine forest and it's various plants, rocks and debris.
longDescription:
Watch the demo videos

Join our Discord channel

Read the documentation and see the changelog


Download the project ini files and put them into your project config folder to get the intended visuals and controls in the Overview map for:

UE4 inis UE5 inis

Please note that Virtual textures need to be enabled in your project settings.

On UE5.1 please set your Lumen scalability settings to HIGH.



A complete environment replicating a Central European Pine forest and it's various plants, rocks and debris.

Procedural placement of foliage and rocks provides a carefully crafted blend between top visual quality and performance.


All materials are using texture packing to save on texture samplers.

The landscape material is equipped with 6 main layers, 3 auto layers, a RemoveSlope, a RemoveFoliage layer and a procedural puddles layer.

A separate landscape layer is available for river- and lakebeds.


Everything is set up to be easily modifiable and intelligently exposes all the parameters you would want to tweak.

The assets and their material system encourage creative asset use and combining, ensuring enormous flexibility.



FEATURES:


  • 141+ professionally captured and handcrafted high quality models from an expert of the field
  • Procedural generation and placement of all included plants and scatter meshes
  • Carefully balanced performance and optimization of every included component
  • Highly adaptable asset materials, including automatically adjusting worldaligned detail layers, 2-blend Moss layers, Wetness layers, vertex paint blend layers, AO mask layers, variation masks and much more
  • Landscape material with up to 11 layers, with Auto layers, sublayers, large and small scale texture variation and normals
  • Adjustable real POM, 4 tap BumpOffset and PDO shadows on landscape layers and meshes (PDO not supported with RVT/Nanite), Tessellation on UE4, VHFM can be used on UE4 and UE5
  • Full RVT support, enabled by default
  • A handcrafted 1km2 example map, showcasing the different biomes and assets, including roads and rivers
  • Texture packed workflow to ensure texture sampling savings and flexibility
  • Dynamic vertex shader based foliage collision for thinner branches and smaller plants, to ensure optimal navigation and realistic interactions even in thick forests
  • Vertex paintable watercover layer, so you can paint water plants onto all included water surfaces
  • User placeable local volumetric fog meshes



ASSET LIST:


Main Trees:

12 variations of Pinus Nigra, pine

5 variations Picea Abies, Spruce


Smaller trees:

3 variations Quercus Petraea, oak


Bushes:

3 variations Berberis Julianae, barberry

2 variations Sibiraea

3 variations Salix Caprea, goat willow

3 variation Salix Petiolaris, slender willow

2 variations of dry undergrowth bushes

1 variation of reeds


Other smaller plants:

1 variation Arctium Lappa, burdoch

1 variation of different fallen leaves

2 variation Hedera Helix, ivy

1 variations of moss patches

2 variations of mushrooms

3 variations Olypodium Vulgare, polypody fern

5 variations of pine scatter, branches and sticks

9 variations of grass and flowers

1 variation of groundcover buckthorn


Rocks:

4 cliff meshes, but two are predominantly used due to their flexibility (+mat variants)

6 large rocks (+ivy variants, +mat variants)

3 medium rocks (+ivy variants, +mat variants)

6 stones (+mat variants)

5 river pebbles


Wood:

34 various scatter meshes, like branches, pine cones, tree stumps, roots, logs and a fallen tree (+mat variants)


Background meshes:

5 background landscapes

1 background cloud sheet asset


Props:

1 road spline assets

1 bridge asset

1 fence asset

1 Austrian postal service milestone

1 spline compatible road guard rail

1 bridge asset


VFX:

1 local volumetric fog asset
technicalDetails:
Features:


  •  Up to 8k texture resolutions (by default limited to 4k), all based on photogrammetry captured surfaces
  •  3D and photometry scanned assets, using professional grade capturing gear
  •  11 landscape layers (including a procedural puddles layer, a RemoveFoliage and a RemoveSlope layer, a dynamic DryGrass sublayer and a dynamic FallenLeaves sublayer)
  • Ready to use Procedural Foliage Spawner volumes
  • Handcrafted 1km2 showcase map
  •  3 extensive master materials (landscape, foliage, static meshes)
  •  Moss layers, Wetness layers, various blend layers
  • POM on landscape layers and static meshes
  • PDO shadows on landscape and static meshes (not compatible with RVT/Nanite)
  • RVT support


Additional Notes:


Please note that shader compilation takes some time on the first startup.


Number of Unique Meshes: 141


Collision: Yes, custom created and created by UE


Vertex Count: 2-150.000 (included, not used for LOD0, but for Nanite meshes)


LODs: 1-6, largely handcrafted, with Billboards for medium to large foliage meshes


Number of Materials and Material Instances: 139


Number of Textures: 281


Texture Resolutions: 1k-8k, but capped to 4k by default (8k source textures available for all larger meshes and landscape)


Supported Development Platforms: PC
